---
layout: layouts/base.njk
---
<h1>{{ site.title }}</h1>
<p class="subtitle">{{ site.tagline }}</p>

<p>
  I created and maintain
  <a href="https://github.com/tree-sitter-perl/tree-sitter-perl">tree-sitter-perl</a>
  (the Perl grammar used in Zed, Neovim, Helix, and Emacs) and authored a
  ~47k-line Perl language server in Rust. I like finding the right primitive,
  then building the elegant thing on top of it. See
  <a href="/projects/">projects</a> for the code.
</p>

<h2>Writing</h2>
<ul>
  {%- for post in collections.posts %}
  <li>
    <a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a>
    <span class="subtitle"><time datetime="{{ post.data.date | isoDate }}">{{ post.data.date | readableDate }}</time></span>
    {%- if post.data.subtitle %}<br /><span class="subtitle">{{ post.data.subtitle }}</span>{% endif %}
  </li>
  {%- else %}
  <li class="subtitle">Nothing published yet — soon.</li>
  {%- endfor %}
</ul>
